args: Well. I'm glad I managed to make this\nmuch progress in the game...
But now I'm so far ahead,\nI can't see anyone else!
I mean, I knew the dice were seriously\nloving me today, but I never thought I'd\ngetting THIS far out in front...
*sniff* Aw man, I hate being alone.\nIt's all scary and junk.

Don't go worryin' yer pretty head about it,
Notte! I'm right here outside the game
board, and I can lend ya a hand no matter
WHERE yer at!
So cheer up, buttercup! I got ya!
*sniff* Th-thanks, Kuzunoha.\nThat makes me feel better.
Welp, even if I am by myself, time to do\nwhat I gotta do and keep pressing on.
Your girl Notte's back on her feet!\nNow let's roll the bones and see what\nkinda square I land on this—AAACK!
STOP! STOP! STOP! STOP! STOP!\nAll players must wait here until one person clears\nthe ＂Heart, Physique, Technique Challenge!＂

Again with these stop squares? Who spit
in your breakfast cereal, ya dumb game?
Also, what the heck is a ＂Heart, Physique,
Technique Challenge＂?
Well, shoot! Reckon I know this one,\nthough I coulda sworn I threw it out...
So whatcha got here are three trials that'll\ntest the challenger's hearts, techniques,\nand physiques.
Wait, why is it here if you threw it out?\nDid your spell going all topsy-turvy send\nthis part to Weirdsville too?
I wouldn't doubt it. And considering\nKuzunoha threw it out, it must be a\nparticularly difficult endeavor.
So what will you do, Notte? You could just\nwait until the rest of your team arrives.
No way! I'm gonna take on any task or trial\nor whatever that stands in my way!
I'm at the top of my game, and I'm gonna\nace this puppy no matter HOW hard it is!
A fine attitude. Let's see what you can do.
OKAY, HOLD THE EVERYTHING!\nWhere the heck did this cliff come from?!
The first trial measures your physique via\nan acrobatic rock-climbing exercise.\nIf you reach the top, you pass.
Oh, that's it? Pfffft! Piece of cake!\nI've got WINGS, remember?!
Which would render this challenge utterly\npointless. You might as well give up if\nyou have so little faith in your strength.
You can't find true strength unless all three\nof the traits are tested—that's the central\nidea behind these trials.
And to that end, there is a built-in security\nsystem to ensure such cheap and tawdry\ntricks won't work.
NO FLYING ALLOWED! ALL CHEATERS WILL\nBE LAUNCHED BACK TO THE STARTING\nPOINT WITH MY POWERFUL BEAK!
Oh man, that beak looks sharp as heck!\nI don't even wanna know how bad that\nwould hurt...

If you don't want to suffer the penalty,
then approach this challenge fair and
square, pull on your big-girl pants,
and get to climbing.

Man, you are SUCH a jerk sometimes!
But fine then! If I have to do it fair and
square, I'm gonna fair and square this
thing right to a total win!
Excellent work, Notte. You really put your\nback into this one.
What, was that supposed to be hard? Ha!\nOkay, so first trial down, right? Bring on\nthe second one, big boy! I'm ready!
The second trial, which we call ＂Besting\nthe Beast,＂ will measure your technique.

Aw, it ain't so bad! Basically the game's
just gonna scan yer memories and recreate
a powerful enemy from yer past so ya
can fight 'em again.

'Fraid I'm about as useless as two buggies
in a one-horse town on this one, even if ya
are just fightin' illusions of folks whatcha
squared off with before.

The one who came up with this one is
about as mean as Lord Seimei himself.
All I can do is cheer ya on from the
sidelines, but hang in there!
Sounds like Kuzunoha's already suffered\na lot at the hands of this trial...
Don't worry, it's not going to kill you.\nNow ready yourself. And...BEGIN!
What in tarnation is ol' Gozu doin' here?!\nWait, maybe it's 'cause'a the fake one\nDoman went and made?

Man, they weren't kidding—this was one
of our toughest fights ever! Heck, we only
beat the guy by all working together, so
how am I supposed to do it all by myself?!
Okay Notte, settle down. You aren't the\nsame weak little faerie that you were\nall the way back when, which means...
Whoa nelly! Since when did Notte\nget to be so durn big?!
Time to prove just how different I am...\nNow behold all the skills I have now that\nI'm all grown-up and stuff!
Yikes! His yelling made a boulder appear!\n...Hey, wait. I remember this! When we\nbroke those boulders, he got weaker!
Memories, don't fail me now!\nHEY, YOU! BIG FELLA! OVER HERE!
Hot dang, it worked! Now's my chance!\nTake the full brunt of my grown-up attacks,\nyou big bully!
Too bad for you, bucko! I know that\nattack, and I know how to dodge it!
*pant* *pant* W-well, Seimei?\nWhat'd you think of my technique?
I saw, and I am impressed. Though I'm at\nsomething of a loss to explain it, you have\nclearly grown—and in more than stature.
Oh, that? Yeah, I wanted to be able to\nprotect folks, so I made myself stronger.
Anyway, we've just got the heart trial left,\nright? Honestly, I feel like I'm ready for\nwhatever this stupid game throws at me!
Darn tootin'! Now keep up the good work\nso ya can really wow Lord Seimei!
I hope you live up to my expectations\nin the third and final trial.
In this one, you must overcome\nyour fear of yourself.
What the? What's that weird haze?\nWhoa! Something's coming out!
Wait, is that...me? Why do I look so sad?\nIs THIS who I face in the third trial?
Yes. I am what you fear most in your\ndeepest, darkest heart.
The unavoidable future where\n{player_name} and Zethia are\ngone and I am all alone.
Faeries live long lives, so all the people\nI love will leave me someday.
My future is so dark and cold...\nI'm so afraid of it...
I've been trying not to see that!\nI've been trying not to think about it!\nAND I DON'T WANNA SEE IT NOW!
